# Swappable providers

All third-party and infrastructure adapters live under
`src/lib/providers/<name>/`. Each exposes an interface + `get<Name>Provider()`
factory (or equivalent facade). Free tier by default; swap = new implementation
+ one factory branch. Job *handlers* (`src/lib/jobs/functions/`) are not
providers — they orchestrate work using provider clients.

| Provider  | Location                              | Default            | Fallback (no API key) |
|-----------|---------------------------------------|--------------------|------------------------|
| Email     | `src/lib/providers/email.ts`          | Resend             | Console logger         |
| SMS       | `src/lib/providers/sms.ts`            | —                  | Console logger         |
| Storage   | `src/lib/providers/storage.ts`        | Supabase Storage   | —                      |
| Search    | `src/lib/providers/search.ts`         | Postgres full-text | —                      |
| Analytics | `src/lib/providers/analytics/`        | PostHog            | No-op                  |
| Jobs      | `src/lib/providers/jobs/`             | Inngest            | Console logger         |
| Redis     | `src/lib/providers/redis/`            | Upstash            | Graceful disable       |

Domain event names live in `src/lib/jobs/catalog.ts` (not a provider).
